{
  "texts": [
    "(B) A sequence visualizing the droplet dynamics during impingement on a hydrophobic substrate obtained by direct numerical simulation.",
    "Physics-based rendering is employed to generate synthetic glare-point shadowgraphy images from the simulated gas-liquid interface geometries.",
    "(C) Schematics of the proposed video-conditioned PINNs (VcPINNs).",
    "Initially, glarepoint shadowgraphy images are processed using a convolutional hourglass network, which extracts pixel-aligned features from the input image at the pixel location (x, y) on the image plane.",
    "Subsequently, temporal correspondences are extracted from the sequence of spatial features."
  ]
